{"build_type":"executable","description":"Filesystem perception tool (replaces tree/ls), AI-native. Request (argv[1]): {\"tree\": {\"path\": \"<dir>\"}}. Emits the COMPLETE recursive structure of the directory as a FLAT array of rows {d:depth, t:dtype, n:name} on stdout — hierarchy lives in the depth column, not in nesting (token-lean, attention-friendly). No depth/limit knobs (lossy); the whole subtree is always returned, scope is chosen by path. Symlinks are emitted but not followed (cycle-safe); permission-denied / non-dir entries degrade to empty, never crash. v1: getdents order (unsorted), structure+type only (size/mode/mtime + sorting + front-coding + dedup are later density layers). Bad request (no argv, unparseable, no arg object, no path) -> clean JSON {error}. Reuses parse_argument_vector_json_request, locate_named_member_inside_mapping, begin_empty_sequence_document_value, walk_filesystem_tree, begin_empty_mapping_document_value, add_str_field, attach_named_member_inside_mapping, emit_result_object_onto_standard_output.","module_name":"produce-flattened-filesystem-hierarchy-representation","package_name":"produce-flattened-filesystem-hierarchy-representation","function_definitions":{"produce-flattened-filesystem-hierarchy-representation":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_trunc","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"truncated"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_hint","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"hint"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"m_hint","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"subtree exceeds the row budget; deeper/later entries are omitted - narrow the path"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_path","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"path"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_root","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"root"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_legend","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"legend"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_tree","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"tree"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_error","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"error"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_code","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"code"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"v_notfound","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"path_not_found"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"m_notfound","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"tree: path does not exist or is not accessible"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"statsize","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":144},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"m_leg","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"d=depth; t=dtype(4=dir,8=file,10=symlink,2=char,6=block,1=fifo,12=sock,0=unknown); n=name; s=size; m=perm bits; l=symlink target. Flat DFS rows; hierarchy is the depth column. Symlinks not followed."},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"m_badreq","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"tree: request must be {tree: {path: <dir>}}"},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"parse-argument-vector-json-request","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"__argc"},{"kind":"var","value":"__argv"}],"result_assignment_variable":"req","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"conditional_branch","condition_type":"numeric_compare","operator":"==","lhs":{"value":"req"},"rhs":{"value":"zero"},"branch_on_success":[{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"begin-empty-mapping-document-value","invocation_arguments":[],"result_assignment_variable":"erA","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"attach-string-member-towards-mapping","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"erA"},{"kind":"var","value":"s_error"},{"kind":"var","value":"m_badreq"}]},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"write-result-object-toward-standard-output","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"erA"}],"result_assignment_variable":"ewA","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"zero"}}],"branch_on_failure":[]},{"instruction_type":"field_read","struct":"json-tree-node","field":"child","base":"req","dest":"reqch"},{"instruction_type":"conditional_branch","condition_type":"numeric_compare","operator":"==","lhs":{"value":"reqch"},"rhs":{"value":"zero"},"branch_on_success":[{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"begin-empty-mapping-document-value","invocation_arguments":[],"result_assignment_variable":"erB","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"attach-string-member-towards-mapping","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"erB"},{"kind":"var","value":"s_error"},{"kind":"var","value":"m_badreq"}]},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"write-resu